00:57:02,399 --> 00:57:05,664
Why is it doctors
are never good at tying ties;

499
00:57:07,203 --> 00:57:08,295
Here.

500
00:57:18,248 --> 00:57:19,340
Hank.

501
00:57:31,261 --> 00:57:32,319
Dan.

502
00:57:35,465 --> 00:57:38,298
- Ride over and fetch Bissonette.
- Yes, sir.

503
00:57:39,402 --> 00:57:40,733
And hurry!

504
00:57:41,404 --> 00:57:45,864
Benjamin, you and Obie
spread some buffalo robes over there.

505
00:58:04,227 --> 00:58:05,694
They want to palaver with us.

506
00:58:30,620 --> 00:58:32,144
What does it mean, John;

507
00:58:33,356 --> 00:58:34,721
lt's hard to tell.

508
00:59:01,251 --> 00:59:02,718
Do as he did.

509
00:59:46,696 --> 00:59:49,529
Be friendly,
but be very careful, mes amis.

510
00:59:50,567 --> 00:59:53,161
Tell the chief he's welcome to our camp.

511
01:00:01,044 --> 01:00:03,171
- You chief;
- l am.

512
01:00:04,514 --> 01:00:08,143
Are you father, little daughter,
Rising Sun;

513
01:00:09,085 --> 01:00:10,643
He means little Myra Thompson.

514
01:00:11,621 --> 01:00:15,182
The little girl has no father.
Only a brother and sister.

515
01:00:19,562 --> 01:00:20,654
Good.

516
01:00:28,471 --> 01:00:32,908
The chief says his gods have told him
to make a trade with the white man.

517
01:00:41,651 --> 01:00:45,678
Those ponies are trained hunters.
The best of the Sioux herd.

518
01:00:45,755 --> 01:00:49,691
With them you will always be able
to keep your cooking pot full of game,

519
01:00:49,759 --> 01:00:51,590
all the way to the Big Water.

520
01:01:23,560 --> 01:01:26,461
The white buffalo robe is sacred.

521
01:01:26,529 --> 01:01:28,292
That robe will protect you

522
01:01:28,364 --> 01:01:30,195
from bad spirits
the rest of your journey.

523
01:01:31,000 --> 01:01:35,528
The ceremonial whistle is a sign
to all Dakota chiefs and braves

524
01:01:35,605 --> 01:01:38,199
that you are friends to be protected.

525
01:01:39,676 --> 01:01:40,768
ln other words, mes amis...

526
01:01:40,843 --> 01:01:43,937
ln other words, he's offering us
a guarantee of safe passage.

527
01:01:44,013 --> 01:01:46,004
What does he want for it;

528
01:01:46,849 --> 01:01:51,047
Well, these gifts
are the greatest he can give.

529
01:01:51,120 --> 01:01:54,180
Them ain't no gifts.
He's looking to trade for something.

530
01:01:54,257 --> 01:01:57,351
- What's he want;
- He wants to trade for the little girl.

531
01:01:57,427 --> 01:01:59,361
Trade;

532
01:01:59,429 --> 01:02:04,025
The chief claims that the great spirit
has spoken to him through Many Stars,

533
01:02:04,100 --> 01:02:06,625
the great medicine man of the Sioux.

534
01:02:07,503 --> 01:02:09,198
He says his gods have told him

535
01:02:09,272 --> 01:02:12,935
that the little one will bring good luck
to the Dakotas.

536
01:02:13,576 --> 01:02:18,104
And the chief also promises
to raise her like a Sioux princess

537
01:02:18,181 --> 01:02:21,514
and take care of her as his own.

538
01:02:22,852 --> 01:02:27,687
ln time, she will become wife
to Little Thunder, his son.

539
01:02:31,861 --> 01:02:33,260
Tell him no.

540
01:02:34,631 --> 01:02:39,000
You understand, Captain, if you try
to take your wagons on from here

541
01:02:39,068 --> 01:02:41,468
without giving up the little one,

542
01:02:41,537 --> 01:02:43,562
he will set the whole Sioux tribe
against you.

543
01:02:43,640 --> 01:02:45,733
Does he think we're as pagan as he is;

544
01:02:46,476 --> 01:02:48,103
The answer is no.

545
01:02:50,313 --> 01:02:51,837
You not father.

546
01:02:53,349 --> 01:02:57,115
- Who speaks for little yellow hair;
- l speak for my sister.

547
01:02:57,186 --> 01:03:00,121
No talk with woman. You not father.

548
01:03:01,090 --> 01:03:04,218
- l'm her father and mother.
- No talk to woman!

549
01:03:04,294 --> 01:03:07,593
You'll talk to me! You pompous savage.

550
01:03:07,664 --> 01:03:10,394
You heard our captain. We won't trade.

551
01:03:11,668 --> 01:03:15,035
How about your son;
Would you trade him to us;

552
01:03:15,104 --> 01:03:17,231
You have gods,
you must believe in them.

553
01:03:17,307 --> 01:03:18,774
Would they let you do this;

554
01:03:23,913 --> 01:03:25,346
Bissonette.

555
01:03:25,415 --> 01:03:29,112
Tell the chief Little Yellow Hair
has no magic for his people.

556
01:03:29,185 --> 01:03:30,243
No medicine.

557
01:03:31,154 --> 01:03:35,056
Tell him she's a little child and
would sicken and die among strangers.

558
01:03:35,124 --> 01:03:38,321
lf Many Stars
has told his chief otherwise...

559
01:03:39,429 --> 01:03:42,694
...he gives bad advice
and his own medicine is weak.

560
01:03:46,969 --> 01:03:48,994
[speaking native language]

561
01:04:01,017 --> 01:04:02,348
Tell him...

562
01:04:03,252 --> 01:04:07,882
Tell him we know the honor he pays us
and the value of the gifts he offers.

563
01:04:09,125 --> 01:04:11,650
But we will not part with the child.

564
01:06:00,670 --> 01:06:02,638
Well, what do we do now;

565
01:06:03,673 --> 01:06:06,699
Camp right where we are
and be as stubborn as he is, l reckon.

566
01:06:06,776 --> 01:06:09,404
l guess they won't try nothing
this close to the fort.

567
01:06:21,324 --> 01:06:24,452
Stay out of it.
We're in enough trouble as it is.

568
01:06:26,329 --> 01:06:28,058
The boy is hurt.

569
01:07:37,366 --> 01:07:40,802
- That was mighty close.
- The boy is badly hurt.

570
01:07:40,870 --> 01:07:42,531
l was talking about you.

571
01:07:42,605 --> 01:07:44,539
You know that tap
you got on the shoulder;

572
01:07:44,607 --> 01:07:48,065
That means your scalp belongs to him
now anytime he wants to claim it.

573
01:07:48,878 --> 01:07:50,903
lf he's as seriously hurt
as l think he is,

574
01:07:50,980 --> 01:07:52,675
he's out to get all of our scalps.

575
01:09:07,590 --> 01:09:09,683
All right. Close up the gates.

576
01:09:17,266 --> 01:09:20,793
- What's the idea closing up the fort;
- A Sioux was just now here.

577
01:09:20,870 --> 01:09:23,168
Old Many Stars cannot bring
the boy around.

578
01:09:23,239 --> 01:09:25,503
Most of the lndians
don't think he can do it.

579
01:09:25,574 --> 01:09:28,771
- Even if he makes the buffalo prayer.
- The buffalo prayer;

580
01:09:28,844 --> 01:09:33,406
Yes. The lndian believes his strength
comes from Tonka Shonka, the buffalo.

581
01:09:34,483 --> 01:09:36,451
And when he has great trouble
he prays to him.

582
01:09:37,153 --> 01:09:39,815
lt's a medicine man's
most powerful medicine.

583
01:09:39,889 --> 01:09:42,414
He only uses it
when everything else fails.

584
01:09:42,491 --> 01:09:45,756
lf that boy dies,
you folks are bad medecin.

585
01:09:45,828 --> 01:09:48,422
We figure your fort's safer
than our wagons.

586
01:09:48,497 --> 01:09:51,466
We wanna bring our women
and young'uns over here.

587
01:09:51,534 --> 01:09:54,992
lf that boy dies,
the Sioux will get the little one,

588
01:09:55,071 --> 01:09:58,336
even if they have to take my fort down
piece by piece.

589
01:09:58,741 --> 01:10:01,073
- You mean you won't help us;
- Did l say that;

590
01:10:02,712 --> 01:10:05,943
lt's just that my fort is not any safer
than your wagons.

591
01:10:07,283 --> 01:10:09,979
lf there's trouble, l'll do what l can.

592
01:13:49,972 --> 01:13:52,338
Well, the old man
made his talk to the buffalo

593
01:13:52,408 --> 01:13:54,171
and it ain't done no good.

594
01:14:04,086 --> 01:14:06,554
You go near that boy now
and they'll kill you.

595
01:14:16,198 --> 01:14:18,189
lt's too late l tell you!

596
01:14:18,734 --> 01:14:21,931
Maybe. But l've got to try.

597
01:14:27,042 --> 01:14:28,634
He'll need help.

598
01:14:32,381 --> 01:14:35,509
The crazy fools.
They ain't got a chance.

599
01:15:04,346 --> 01:15:08,214
White man, big medicine.

600
01:15:08,817 --> 01:15:12,275
Come to help you save boy's life.

601
01:15:12,988 --> 01:15:14,148
Go!

602
01:15:14,690 --> 01:15:18,854
Two medicines better than one.

603
01:15:30,873 --> 01:15:33,899
Prayers of Many Stars good.

604
01:15:34,410 --> 01:15:36,275
Great Spirit hear.

605
01:15:37,379 --> 01:15:41,042
Your medicine bring white doctor.

606
01:15:41,817 --> 01:15:44,547
Many Stars have big magic.

607
01:15:45,654 --> 01:15:47,144
Now use magic.

608
01:16:04,073 --> 01:16:06,871
The boy's mother
begging a chance for us.

609
01:16:09,745 --> 01:16:12,873
Well, if l can help the boy,
the old man can claim the credit.

610
01:16:12,948 --> 01:16:15,439
- He ought to see that.
- Don't worry.

611
01:16:16,085 --> 01:16:19,418
He ain't missing no bets.
Not that old devil.

612
01:16:23,025 --> 01:16:26,483
Right now he's figuring out
who he'll blame if the boy dies,

613
01:16:26,562 --> 01:16:28,052
after you work on him.

614
01:16:28,831 --> 01:16:30,492
You think of that.

615
01:18:19,274 --> 01:18:20,605
This is the trouble.

616
01:18:23,779 --> 01:18:25,474
lt's a broken clavicle.

617
01:18:27,149 --> 01:18:30,050
Bone splinters punctured a vein
in the neck.

618
01:18:30,652 --> 01:18:33,883
lnternal bleeding and swelling
are interfering with his breathing.

619
01:18:37,125 --> 01:18:38,956
l'll try to relieve the pressure.

620
01:18:39,661 --> 01:18:41,185
How much chance;

621
01:18:41,263 --> 01:18:43,026
Hours ago,
would've been fairly simple.

622
01:18:44,266 --> 01:18:47,360
- And now;
- l don't know.

623
01:22:46,241 --> 01:22:48,232
How does it feel
to be a mighty important man

624
01:22:48,310 --> 01:22:50,073
instead of a mighty dead one;

625
01:22:57,586 --> 01:22:59,679
- We're all ready.
- Oh, yeah;

626
01:24:14,529 --> 01:24:15,757
You are friend.

627
01:24:16,765 --> 01:24:20,724
Wolfs Brother of the Dakotas
take you safe to Big Water.

628
01:24:41,256 --> 01:24:43,417
Like to take my place up in front, Dan;

629
01:24:44,225 --> 01:24:45,954
Sure. Come on, Chieftain.

630
01:25:17,258 --> 01:25:20,193
Medical man's got more to do
than pound a saddle all day.

631
01:25:22,530 --> 01:25:23,758
Yo! Hup!

632
01:25:24,332 --> 01:25:28,166
Roll your wagons!

633
01:25:32,540 --> 01:25:35,031
 Westward roll the wagons

634
01:25:35,110 --> 01:25:37,340
 Always westward roll

635
01:25:37,412 --> 01:25:39,937
 Westward roll the wagons

636
01:25:40,015 --> 01:25:42,040
 For Oregon's our goal

637
01:25:44,686 --> 01:25:46,881
 There's magic in the wind

638
01:25:46,955 --> 01:25:49,253
 And a brightness in the sky

639
01:25:49,324 --> 01:25:51,121
 There's a promised land awaitin'

640
01:25:51,192 --> 01:25:53,592
 And we'll get there by and by

641
01:25:53,662 --> 01:25:56,062
 Westward roll the wagons

642
01:25:56,131 --> 01:25:58,292
 Westward roll them far

643
01:25:58,366 --> 01:26:01,164
 Westward roll the wagons

644
01:26:01,236 --> 01:26:02,931
 Toward the western star

645
01:26:03,004 --> 01:26:06,235
 Westward roll, westward roll

646
01:26:06,307 --> 01:26:12,303
 Westward roll 